While technical excellence is relatively easy to achieve, in today’s world, success requires ongoing learning. “Twenty years ago, you’d come out of university and that was the last time you’d ever have to learn anything. Now the half-life of knowledge is so short that you have to work continually to maintain your leading edge,” says career and self-leadership coach Briony Liber. So whether you go back to university or find professional courses to attend, constant upskilling is vital. What’s more difficult is developing your emotional quotient. 